### Load standardpackages

1 Data & Preprocessing

1.1 Corpus Creation

  1. Scopus download of documents retrieved from search strings from Lorentzen (2010). Limited to LANGUAGE = ENGLISH AND TYPE = (ARTICLE) AND SRCTYPE=(JOURNAL). Scopus1 is created from searching all Scopuss subject areas, and applying additional filtering on the resulting set of 5142 publications. Namely,I performed second filtering based on search string product OR process OR organisational innovation or institution*. This type of criteria is applied manually in Lorentzen (2010). Scopus2 and Scopus3 are generated without second filtering. Scopus2 is limited to social science subject areas, whereas Scopus3 is limited to social science subject areas, excluding Art&Humanities and Psychology.
  2. WoS download of documents retrieved from search string from Lorentzen (2010). Limited to LANGUAGE = ENGLISH AND TYPE = (ARTICLE) AND SRCTYPE=(JOURNAL). For wos1 same limitations as in Scopus1.That lead to initial 6933 publications. Wos2 is limited to Social Sciences Citation Index (SSCI), and no second filtering is applied.

That leads to following corpus sizes:

1.2 Preprocessing

M_wos2$JI

1.2.1 Genral cleaning

# Filtering out unrelated journals
M_wos2 %<>% 
  filter(!(JI %in% c('LANCET', 'PLOS MED.', 'P. NATL. ACAD. SCI. USA'))) %>%
  as.data.frame()

1.2.2 Identifying countries

country_list <- c("Afghanistan", "Burkina Faso" ,  "Burundi" ,  "Central African Republic" ,  "Chad" ,  "Congo" ,  "Eritrea" ,  "Ethiopia" ,  "Gambia" ,  "Guinea" ,  "Guinea-Bissau" ,  "Haiti" ,  "Democratic People's Republic Korea" ,  "Liberia" ,  "Madagascar" ,  "Malawi" ,  "Mali" ,  "Mozambique" ,  "Niger" ,  "Rwanda" ,  "Sierra Leone" ,  "Somalia" ,  "South Sudan" ,  "Sudan" ,  "Syrian Arab Republic" ,  "Tajikistan" ,  "Togo" ,  "Uganda" ,  "Yemen") %>% str_to_lower()
countries_wos2 <- M_wos2 %>%
  mutate(text = paste(TI, AB, DE, ID, sep = ' ') %>% str_to_lower()) %>%
  mutate(countries = text %>% str_extract_all(paste(country_list, collapse="|")) ) %>%
  select(UT, countries) %>%
  unnest(countries) %>%
  distinct(UT, countries) %>%
  nest(countries) %>% 
  rename(countries = data) %>%
  rowwise() %>%
    mutate(countries = countries %>% as.character(),
    n_countries = countries %>% length()) %>%
  ungroup()
M_wos2 %<>%
  left_join(countries_wos2, by = 'UT')
M_wos2 %<>%
  replace_na(list('n_countries' = 0))

5 Create keyword co-occurrences network & plot the network

5.1 Scopus1


NetMatrix_scopus1 <- biblioNetwork(M_scopus1, analysis = "co-occurrences", network = "keywords", sep = ";")

net_scopus1=networkPlot(NetMatrix_scopus1, normalize="association", weighted=T, n = 30, Title = "Keyword Co-occurrences", type = "fruchterman", size=T,edgesize = 5,labelsize=0.7)

5.2 Scopus3


NetMatrix_scopus3 <- biblioNetwork(M_scopus3, analysis = "co-occurrences", network = "keywords", sep = ";")
